<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,280,152,176]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Name:</emphasis>
To emphasize the animal coming on a lonely cave, “ 
<taxonomicName box="[868,964,151,175]" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Hyleoglomeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Glomerida" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heshang">heshang</taxonomicName>
” in Chinese meaning a “monk”; a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/214395/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" targetBox="[163,1435,281,1415]" targetPageId="16">
